According to the CDC, about 160,000 Americans died of lung cancer in 2004 (only 2/3 of which were smokers).  There are over 45 million American smokers.  Thats less than 1%.<br />
<br />
Smokings bad for you -- but its bad for you on a level like stress is bad for you, like living in a city is bad for you, like not getting enough exercise is bad for you.   NOT like heroin is bad for you.
                  
